65:- when workflow-level changes were being discussed, the user repeatedly steered the run back into planning/discussion before more implementation -> for broad AreaMatrix workflow changes, discuss the lifecycle and boundary first instead of jumping straight into code [Task 2]
75:- The current AreaMatrix workflow should be explained as three distinct layers: `docs/` as SSOT, `workflow/` for version/planning lifecycle, and `tasks/prompts/**` as the approved live queue; `./task-loop` only executes the queue instead of making requirement decisions [Task 1]
76:- A durable current-workflow chain is: `docs -> workflow/templates -> workflow/versions/v*/discussion -> middle-layer -> changes -> plans -> drafts -> queue -> promotion preview -> tasks/prompts/** -> ./task-loop run -> archive` [Task 1]
78:- `tasks/prompts/_shared/progress.json` is the primary progress source; `.codex/task-loop-state.txt` is legacy compatibility only [Task 1]
79:- Copy-ready prompts may modify files; verify-ready prompts are read-only; only `VERIFY_RESULT: PASS` allows the runner to advance to the next task [Task 1]
80:- Runner evidence is stored under `.codex/task-loop-logs/<run_id>/...`, `.codex/task-loop-runs/<run_id>/summary.json`, and `.codex/task-loop-runs/index.json` [Task 1]
81:- `./task-loop drain`, `resume-failed`, `resume-stale`, `clear-stale`, and `reset-progress` have distinct recovery meanings and should be explained as different runtime recovery tools, not treated as aliases [Task 1]
86:- In the latest current-workflow evidence, `./task-loop status` showed `lock_alive: yes`, `lock_operation: run`, and `live_activity: verify task=4-1/task-115 attempt=3 status=running`; when `live_activity_log_state: missing` but the child is alive, describe it as a no-output wait state rather than failure [Task 1]
88:- For `当前 phase-4 在做什么` questions, the real source of truth is the live prompt label from `./task-loop status` plus the corresponding manifest/task file. In this refreshed rollout, the active phase-4 task resolved to `4-1/task-127`, and the underlying example translation path still points through `S2-03 saved-search-sheet + C2-03 saved-search-crud`, which shows why “phase4” can still mean Stage 2 saved-search / Smart List work rather than Stage 4 multiplatform execution [Task 4]
90:- For HR-facing AreaMatrix explanations, the most reusable structure is: product value first, then the user’s responsibility/workflow, then the stack (`Rust core + SQLite + UniFFI + SwiftUI/AppKit on macOS`), then one or two differentiators such as docs-first planning, task splitting, automatic execution, read-only acceptance, and repair closure [Task 5]
91:- The repo’s architecture docs describe AreaMatrix as `Core + Shell` / layered design, so recruiter-facing explanations should prefer that wording over a generic “后端/前端” split [Task 5]
92:- A strong copy-ready summary for interview use is: AreaMatrix is a macOS native file-management tool that uses a Rust core to support safe repository adoption, indexing, drag-in import, search, Smart Lists, AI-assisted expansion, and later multi-platform extension [Task 5]
98:- `./dev workflow init --version <v*>` is the standard way to create a new AreaMatrix version skeleton. It generates `version.yaml`, a root README, the `discussion/` trio, plus README placeholders for `changes/`, `plans/`, `drafts/`, `queue/`, and `promotion/` [Task 3]
103:- Verification for this workflow family included `python3 -m py_compile scripts/task_loop/*.py scripts/dev_tools/*.py`, plus `./dev workflow doctor`, `./dev workflow status`, `./dev workflow discuss --version v2 doctor`, `./dev changes doctor`, `./task-loop check`, `./dev check governance`, `./dev check skills`, `./dev check prompts`, and `./dev check diff` [Task 2][Task 3]
107:- Symptom: a workflow explanation sounds generic or stale. Cause: it was answered from memory or design intent instead of current repo evidence. Fix: read `tasks/prompts/README.md`, `scripts/task_loop.md`, `.ai-governance/workflows/prompt-task-runtime.md`, `workflow/README.md`, `workflow/AGENTS.md`, then capture `prompt_pipeline.py status`, `./task-loop status`, and `./dev workflow status` before summarizing [Task 1]
109:- Symptom: a live task shows `copy_log=missing` and the explanation assumes completion or failure. Cause: missing output was treated as terminal state. Fix: if the child is still alive, explain it as a no-output wait state and keep `./task-loop status` as first-class runtime evidence [Task 1]
110:- Symptom: the explanation names the wrong current task or old file path. Cause: the active task label was inferred from older memory or a stale filename guess. Fix: trace `./task-loop status` -> prompt/manifests -> exact task file, then restate the current task using the live manifest label [Task 1]
111:- Symptom: phase naming makes the answer drift toward “Stage 4 multiplatform is running now”. Cause: the agent inferred from the phase title or filename instead of opening the live prompt/task mapping. Fix: trace `./task-loop status` -> prompt path -> `tasks/prompts/_shared/manifests/phase-4.md` -> exact task file before translating the current work [Task 4]
