290:- when the user asked “那当前工作流的整个执行顺序输出给我看看” and then narrowed to “把phase4详细解释一下” -> future answers should start from actual `prompt_pipeline.py` / `./task-loop status` evidence, then translate the queue into plain-language product meaning [Task 13]
292:- when the user asked “这个现在是在干嘛” and later “那现在呢，为啥跑了一个半小时去” -> translate `./task-loop status` into plain Chinese state words like waiting, stalled, restarting, or progressing, instead of pasting raw heartbeat fields [Task 14]
297:- `./task-loop status` is the quickest source of truth for whether a long run is healthy, stale, or blocked on a child process; in this incident it exposed `live_activity`, `live_activity_log_state`, and later the cleared stale state [Task 1]
299:- `tasks/prompts/_shared/prompt_pipeline_lib/rendering.py` is the central copy-ready / verify-ready prompt renderer; adding “ordinary atomic tasks must not escalate to cargo test --workspace / ./dev check core / ./dev check all” there propagates across the exported prompt set [Task 1][Task 10]
300:- `.codex/skills-src/areamatrix-validation-driver/references/validation-matrix.md` and `scripts/task_loop/self_check.py` are the right guardrails for keeping the broad Rust Core matrix out of ordinary atomic tasks [Task 1][Task 10]
301:- After the copy-stage boundary fix, `python3 tasks/prompts/_shared/prompt_pipeline.py export --all` still reported `copy-ready: 637` and `verify-ready: 637`; the extra file in copy-ready was only `README.md`, so the real task count stayed 637 [Task 1]
303:- After the resplit, the prompt system supports both copy-ready and verify-ready output from the same task source, and the rendered prompt includes task kind, UX bindings, Core bindings, and whether file edits are allowed [Task 3]
306:- The task-loop runner now uses `codex exec` as the actual executor, with shell scripts orchestrating copy-ready execution and read-only verify-ready checks [Task 5]
307:- The primary progress source is `tasks/prompts/_shared/progress.json`; the old `.codex/task-loop-state.txt` is compatibility input only [Task 5]
309:- The loop writes resumable evidence into `.codex/task-loop-logs/<timestamp>/<phase>/`, `.codex/task-loop-runs/<run_id>/summary.json`, and `.codex/task-loop-runs/index.json`, and uses a lock dir to avoid concurrent writers [Task 5]
312:- The governance pack made `CODE_REVIEW.md`, `docs/development/dependency-policy.md`, `docs/development/ci-governance.md`, `.github/CODEOWNERS`, `SECURITY.md`, and `scripts/check-governance.sh` the core repo-level governance anchors; `governance-ci.yml` runs governance, skill, task-loop, prompt doctor, and diff checks on every PR/main push [Task 6]
314:- `tasks/prompts/_shared/progress.json` is the primary source of truth for completed/in-progress AreaMatrix task state; `python3 tasks/prompts/_shared/prompt_pipeline.py doctor`, `python3 tasks/prompts/_shared/prompt_pipeline.py status`, and `bash scripts/run_area_matrix_task_pipeline.sh --status` are the live health/state trio [Task 7]
315:- In the new task-loop evidence, the library reported `tasks: 637` with `phase-0: 15`, `phase-1: 124`, `phase-2: 106`, `phase-3: 5`, `phase-4: 387`; later live states included `completed: 94` with `1-4/task-11` active, and then `completed: 119`, `in_progress: 1`, current `1-5/task-06` [Task 7][Task 9]
316:- A safe stop is `Ctrl+C` in the launcher terminal or `kill -TERM <pid>` against the runner process group, followed by `bash scripts/run_area_matrix_task_pipeline.sh --status`; if the runner is active and `.codex/task-loop-lock/` is live, do not start a second runner [Task 7]
332:- The verify-ready hard boundary now needs to stay visible in generated prompts: “Manifest Validation 是本次验收可主动运行命令的硬上限”; prompt generation and `scripts/task_loop/self_check.py` both enforce it, while true integration/stage/closeout prompts remain allowed broad-gate exceptions [Task 10]
333:- `./task-loop status` plus `./task-loop drain` is the correct pair for long-running verify incidents: status tells whether the live child is stuck in copy/verify with stale/missing log progress; drain asks the runner to stop after the current task instead of rolling into the next one [Task 10]
334:- Retry attempts reuse the same copy-ready / verify-ready task files; attempt 2+ differs only by the runner’s injected retry prompt and verify suffix, so retry broadening bugs must be fixed in `scripts/task_loop/runner.py` rather than in generated prompt bodies [Task 11]
336:- `./task-loop status` is the authoritative source for live verify state, including `live_activity`, `alive`, `log_state`, `no_output_elapsed`, `no_output_timeout`, and `child_restart`; use it before interpreting a long-running verify [Task 14]
343:- Symptom: a long run looks ambiguous because the log is missing. Cause: the child process may still be alive and validating too broadly. Fix: check `./task-loop status` plus `ps` before assuming the runner is merely slow or dead [Task 1]
344:- Symptom: stale state remains after killing a runaway child. Cause: the runner lock/progress still records an in-progress task. Fix: use `./task-loop clear-stale` after confirming the live child is gone, then audit the worktree before resuming [Task 1]
345:- Symptom: prompt system exists, but still feels too coarse for the user’s execution standard. Cause: early task slices were broad implementation bundles. Fix: split into contract/implementation/validation/integration-verify chains and expose verify-ready prompts explicitly [Task 3]
348:- Symptom: the first pass of the task-loop only partially covered the desired silent behavior. Cause: it lacked explicit risk gating, shared progress, recovery, and Git checkpointing. Fix: add those controls before claiming the loop is truly resumable or operable [Task 5]
355:- Symptom: an ordinary atomic verify-ready task runs for a long time and drifts into `cargo test --workspace`. Cause: generated verify-ready prompt embedded a broad Rust Core matrix instead of a task-scoped validation contract. Fix: stop the live child, patch prompt generation, regenerate prompts, and make `./task-loop check` reject ordinary prompts that still contain broad workspace fallback [Task 10]
356:- Symptom: a self-check meant to prevent broad gates suddenly flags legitimate integration/stage prompts. Cause: the guard treated all verify-ready prompts the same. Fix: keep explicit exception handling for `core-integration-verify`, stage verify, and closeout-style prompts [Task 10]
360:- Symptom: the task-loop looks “stuck” because the log is missing for a long time. Cause: the runner may still be healthy while a child `codex exec` is alive and not writing fresh output. Fix: separate “runner alive / lock alive” from “child writing logs”, and inspect `./task-loop status`, `./dev status --verbose`, process state, and the active attempt logs before calling it a stall [Task 14]
362:- Symptom: a verify has run for about 1.5 hours with no output and the explanation assumes it is still validating. Cause: long duration was treated as progress instead of silence. Fix: check `./task-loop status` twice plus `ps`; if `log_state: missing` transitions to `restart_wait` and `alive=no`, explain it as a watchdog timeout/restart rather than active validation [Task 14]
