703:- `python3 tasks/prompts/_shared/prompt_pipeline.py doctor` is the fastest prompt-library health check. In these runs it reported `tasks: 127`, `task slices: 1117/1118` depending on the exact checkout moment, `manifest missing expected total: 0`, and zero missing copy-ready / verify-ready / slice markers [Task 1][Task 2]
705:- `GIT_BRANCH_POLICY=auto` on `main` creates a `codex/areasong-task-loop-<run_id>` checkpoint branch automatically; switch to `GIT_BRANCH_POLICY=current` only if the user explicitly wants each PASS committed on the current branch [Task 1]
707:- PASS alone was not sufficient before the fix: final `.codex/task-loop-runs/summary.json` and `index.json` writes could still dirty the worktree after checkpoint. The durable fix was to add `finalize-evidence` in `scripts/task_loop_git.py` and call it from `scripts/run_areasong_task_pipeline.sh` so run-summary evidence is checkpointed after completion [Task 2]
708:- A slice can be `verify_result: pass` while the task-loop still fails because `git_checkpoint_status=git_diff_check_failed`; checkpoint scope validation is a separate gate from verify, and `task_loop_git.py check-scope` rejects dirty paths outside the current slice/evidence scope [Task 4]
712:- `frontend/tsconfig.json` changing from `"incremental": true` to `false` is the main repo-level prevention step for this class of task-loop checkpoint drift [Task 5]
