    45	
    46	- Atomic Core task: `./dev check task <label>`.
    47	- Core capability integration verify: `./dev check task <label>`.
    48	- Page feature or page integration task: `./dev check task <label>`.
    49	- Stage/foundation closeout or release task: `./dev check all`.
    50	
    51	`./dev check task <label>` always runs prompt doctor and diff checks, then chooses
    52	the smallest repo-local implementation gate for that task:
    53	
    54	- Atomic Core task: targeted Rust test binaries only, such as
    55	  `cargo test --test <target> -- --nocapture`.
    56	- Core capability integration verify: targeted Rust test binaries plus the Core
    57	  quality gate (`cargo fmt --all -- --check` and
    58	  `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`).
    59	- Mission-Critical file-safety, DB, staging, recovery, sync, import, migration,
    60	  reindex, or user-file boundary: widen to the Core quality gate.
    61	- Page feature or page integration task: macOS build gate.
    62	- Stage/foundation closeout or release task: `./dev check all`.
    63	
    64	Agents may run additional targeted tests when the task or observed changes need
    65	more evidence, but the manifest should reserve `./dev check all` for integration
    66	or release boundaries.
    67	
    68	Atomic Core tasks without a targeted test mapping must fail with a mapping error
    69	instead of silently falling back to `cargo test --workspace`. Add the missing
    70	mapping in `scripts/dev_tools/checks.py`, run an explicit `./dev check core` or
    71	`./dev check all` for a broad gate, or set `AREAMATRIX_TASK_CHECK_FULL_FALLBACK=1`
    72	only when an emergency full fallback is intentionally chosen.
    73	
    74	During copy-ready execution, the task manifest `Validation` is the upper bound
    75	for ordinary atomic tasks. Do not turn a normal `./dev check task <label>` into
    76	`cargo test --workspace`, `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features`,
    77	`./dev check core`, or `./dev check all` just because files under `core/**`
    78	changed. The path-based Rust Core row below is for broad manual gates,
    79	integration / release boundaries, or explicit escalation, not the default for
    80	every Core prompt task.
    81	
    82	## Rust Core
    83	
    84	Required for `core/**`:
    85	
    86	```bash
    87	cd core && cargo fmt --all -- --check
    88	cd core && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings
    89	cd core && cargo test --workspace
    90	```
    91	
    92	If a task manifest names narrower tests, run those too. Do not skip the manifest validation command just because broad tests pass.
    93	
    94	## macOS App
    95	
    96	Required for `apps/macos/**`:
    97	
    98	```bash
    99	xcodebuild -project apps/macos/AreaMatrix.xcodeproj -scheme AreaMatrix -destination 'platform=macOS,arch=arm64' build CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO
   100	./dev test macos
   101	```
   102	
   103	`./dev test macos` is the local macOS unit-test gate. It first runs the
   104	standard `xcodebuild test` command. Only when the failure log explicitly points
   105	to a local `testmanagerd` sandbox restriction may it reuse the built XCTest
   106	bundle through `xcrun xctest`. Non-sandbox failures, assertion failures, build
   107	failures, or link failures still fail the validation.
   108	
   109	If Xcode is unavailable, report it as blocked with exact command and error.
   110	
   111	For SwiftUI page or interaction tasks, add Computer Use UI smoke evidence when
   112	the task needs a real window, click, menu, input, screenshot, or visible state
   113	check. Follow `.codex/references/computer-use-macos-ui-smoke-runbook.md`.
   114	This evidence is supplemental and does not replace `xcodebuild`, `./dev test
   115	macos`, SwiftLint / SwiftFormat, Rust tests, prompt verify, or docs / UDL / Core
   116	API checks.
   117	
   118	## Docs Only
   119	
   120	Docs-only changes do not need code tests by default. Still run targeted checks when the docs affect executable surfaces:
   121	
   122	- Prompt docs or manifests: run `doctor`.
   123	- API or UDL docs: inspect `docs/api/core-api.md` and `core/area_matrix.udl` alignment.
   124	- UX page specs with control maps: run page audit when prompt coverage can drift.
   125	- Skill docs: run `./dev check skills`.
   126	
   127	## Mixed Changes
   128	
   129	For mixed changes, combine relevant rows. Examples:
   130	
   131	- `core/**` + `docs/api/**`: run Rust core checks and doc-sync checks.
   132	- `tasks/prompts/**` + `scripts/**`: run prompt doctor and script syntax/status/dry-run checks.
   133	- file safety behavior + docs: run implementation tests plus file-safety acceptance evidence.
   134	- governance docs + skills + CI: run governance check, skill health, prompt doctor, and YAML parse.
   135	
   136	## When To Widen
   137	
   138	Widen validation when:
   139	
   140	- change crosses Core and macOS boundary
   141	- task is `Mission-Critical`
   142	- behavior touches user files, DB, staging, or external sync
   143	- manifest validation lists broader commands
   144	- engineering-quality review finds unclear flow, missing error handling, missing comments/rustdoc, or insufficient tests
   145	- code review, dependency, license, security, privacy, CI, or Git evidence has unresolved blockers
   146	- prior verify failed for missing evidence

